observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the:
a. Inventory Committee to continue its efforts in completing the physical count of the properties of the Municipality and prepare and submit the required report thereon, in proper form, summarized according to type of PPE and properly accomplished and in all particulars, in accordance with Section 124 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I;
b. GSO and the Municipal Accountant to maintain a complete and updated PCs and PPELCs, respectively, and issue ARE to pinpoint accountability based on the reconciled inventory report of PPE;
c. GSO to continue its efforts in completion of the Municipal PPELCs and PCs for the Local Road Network; and
d. Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjustments to correct the over provision for depreciation in the Machinery and Equipment accounts and computing depreciation thereafter, exercise caution in providing depreciation on PPE.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a. Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory of all the PPE including the Road Network System of the Municipality and prepare and submit the required report thereon, in proper form, summarized according to type of PPE and properly accomplished in all particulars, in accordance with Section 124 of MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I and Item VI of COA Circular No. 2015-008. Any discrepancies between the inventory report and the accounting and property records, should be investigated and make necessary adjustments where the error was committed;
b. GSO and the Municipal Accountant to maintain a complete and updated PCs and PPELCs, respectively, and issue ARE to pinpoint accountability based on the reconciled inventory report of PPE;
c. Municipal Engineer to expedite the submission of the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects of the Municipality;
d. GSO to maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete LRNPC for all roads and its components; and
e. Municipal Accountant to disclose in the Notes to the Financial Statements the total road network system of the Municipality at year-end.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
a. OIC-Municipal Treasurer in coordination with the Municipal Accountant to return to source agencies or to Bureau of the Treasury the amount due to National Agencies to relieve the Municipality for any accountability/liability;
b. Municipal Accountant to revert to Validated of existing records and appropriate adjustments were made; Government Equity, with concurrence of the Sangguniang Bayan the recorded obligation without proper documents and record only obligation with proper and complete documentations.

a. Inventory Committee to conduct the physical count of all fixed assets of the Municipality; and submit the properly accomplished Inventory Report to the Auditor concerned not later than January 31 of each year, pursuant to Section 124 of the MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I and reconcile the reports with the accounting and property records, investigate any discrepancy that may exist thereafter and effect the necessary corrections where needed;
b. Property Officer/GSO to maintain property cards and immediately record the property delivered upon acceptance and inspection, pursuant to Section 119 of MNGAS for LGUs, Volume I; Moreover, ensure that ARE were properly accomplished and renew the same every three years to update signature and information listed in the RPCPPE;
c. Municipal Accountant to maintain property ledger cards and record the deliveries upon receipt of Acceptance and Inspection Report (AIR) and other supporting documents in the appropriate ledger cards; and
d. Concerned Municipal Officials to coordinate with the donors of the motor vehicles for the needed documents for its immediate recording in the books and subsequently compute and record the accumulated depreciation of the said motor vehicles.
